    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-01-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-01-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="262"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                <head>262. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_KJF2" type="from"
                        >Kennedy</persName> to the Administrator of the Agency for International
                    Development (<persName corresp="#p_HF5" type="to">Hamilton</persName>)<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d262fn1">Source: Kennedy Library, National
                        Security Files, Countries Series, British Guiana II. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-01-12">January 12, 1962</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>British Guiana</item>
                </list>
                <p>I wish immediate steps to be taken to get an economic mission to British Guiana
                    by February 15 and to expand technical assistance to the level of $1.5 million.
                    I am also requesting immediate action to intensify our observations of political
                    developments in British Guiana and by this and other means extend our program of
                    reinsurance in case the situation should show signs of going sour.</p>
                <p>Could you report to me as soon as possible concerning your action on this
                        matter.<note n="2" xml:id="d262fn2">Printed from an unsigned copy.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
